@page "/about"

<PageTitle>About - Murder Mystery Party</PageTitle>

<div class="about-container">
    <div class="about-header">
        <h1 class="about-title">About This App</h1>
        <h2 class="about-subtitle">Murder Mystery Dinner Party - 1920's SpeakEasy Gala 2026</h2>
    </div>

    <section class="about-section">
        <h3>Technologies</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Blazor WebAssembly (.NET 8)</li>
            <li>ASP.NET Core SignalR (Round unlocks)</li>
            <li>Azure App Service (SignalR hub hosting for push notifications)</li>
            <li>GitHub Pages (client hosting)</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
        <h3>Architecture</h3>
        <p>
            The client is a Blazor WebAssembly app that runs entirely in the browser. Game state is managed
            in client-side services. Round unlocks are broadcast to all connected players through a
            separate SignalR hub server. This keeps the client lightweight while enabling real-time updates.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
        <h3>Author</h3>
        <p>Jim Byer, with the aid of GitHub Copilot AI.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="about-actions">
        <a href="" class="back-home-btn">🏠 Back to Home</a>
    </div>
</div>
